    <ul>
      <li>Double-check your selections carefully.</li>
      <li>Select <strong>Next</strong>.</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>On <strong>Advanced settings</strong> set the following:
    <ul>
      <li>Ensure <strong>Enable semantic ranker</strong> is selected.</li>
      <li>If it isn=E2=80=99t already selected, set <strong>Schedule</stron=
g> to <strong>Once</strong>.</li>
      <li>Select <strong>Next</strong>.</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>On <strong>Review and create</strong> set <strong>Objects name prefix=
</strong> to <code>margies-index</code> and then select <strong>Create</str=
ong>.</li>
  <li>You may close the success notification.</li>
  <li>In the navigation pane on the left, under <strong>Search management</=
strong>, view the <strong>Indexers</strong> page. The <strong>margies-index=
-indexer</strong> should appear. Wait a few minutes, and click <strong>&amp=
;orarr; Refresh</strong> until the <strong>Status</strong> indicates <stron=
g>Success</strong>.</li>
</ol>

<h2 id=3D"search-the-index">Search the index</h2>

<p>Now that you have an index, you can search it.</p>

<ol>
  <li>Return to the <strong>Overview</strong> page for your Azure AI Search=
 resource, and on the toolbar, select <strong>Search explorer</strong>.</li=
>
  <li>
    <p>In Search explorer, in the <strong>Query string</strong> box, enter =
<code>*</code> (a single asterisk) and then select <strong>Search</strong>.=
</p>

    <p>This query retrieves all documents in the index in JSON format. Exam=
ine the results and note the fields for each document, which include docume=
nt content, metadata, and enriched data extracted by the cognitive skills.<=
/p>
